  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed for the primary hemolysis QoI; all 13 credibility factors are assessed and achievedLevel meets or exceeds requiredLevel. Decision: Accepted. This package is a synthetic adversarial sample designed to trigger COMPOUND-01: the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical), and one validation result omits hasUncertaintyQuantification (W-AL-01, High).",
